The paper focuses on zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the construction of embedding space, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on standard zero-shot learning datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
